Reasoning: The paper focuses on the combinatorial complexity of formal languages, which is a topic closely related to formal language theory (cs.FL). The study of combinatorial complexity also involves combinatorics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant as it deals with the quantification of information content in languages. Finally, the study of formal languages and their properties can also be considered a topic in mathematical logic (cs.LO).
